%% Transform Status State Machine
%% Lifecycle of cleaning/filter/alias/map transforms

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> enabled : POST /api/datasets/{id}/transforms\n(batch create)

    enabled --> disabled : undoCleaningTransform\n(action: disable)
    disabled --> enabled : reEnableCleaningTransform

    enabled --> deleted : undoCleaningTransform\n(action: delete)
    disabled --> deleted : undoCleaningTransform\n(action: delete)

    deleted --> [*] : Soft-deleted\n(excluded from all queries)

    note right of enabled
        Transform is active in the
        3-stage Ibis pipeline:
        MUTATE → FILTER → RENAME
    end note

    note right of disabled
        Transform is preserved in DB
        but skipped during pipeline
        execution. Reversible.
    end note

    note left of deleted
        Soft delete — record remains
        in DB with status="deleted".
        Not reversible via API.
    end note

    state enabled {
        [*] --> applied
        applied --> previewing : New preview requested
        previewing --> applied : Preview confirmed
    }
